05/04/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Milorad Dodik is calling on war crimes indictees wanted by the UN tribunal to turn themselves in voluntarily.
Speaking on Tuesday (4 April), he also urged anyone with information about fugitives to contact RS authorities.
Dodik stressed that full collaboration with the tribunal would be in the interest of RS.
(RTRS, RS Government Web site - 04/04/06)
